line_1: Burnet and Heylyn, Hobbes and Lock:
line_2: From Break-fast reads, 'till twelve a Clock,

line_1: Miss in a hurry bursts the lock,
line_2: To get clean sleeves to hide her smock;

line_1: Slips the slave's collar on, and snaps the lock.
line_2: Gives liberty the last, the mortal shock,

line_1: And house with Montagne now, or now with Lock.
line_2: As drives the  storm, at any door I knock,

line_1: So, Sir, as sure as Key or Lock —
line_2: Your Servant Sir — at Six a Clock.

line_1: Do thou, Crispissa, tend her fav'rite Lock;
line_2: Ariel himself shall be the Guard of Shock.
